  <sections xmi:id="_mALxwM1uEd6r0fGOs-z5sw" name="Select a viewpoint" guid="_mALxwM1uEd6r0fGOs-z5sw">
    <sectionDescription>Select the system aspects (reflected in a viewpoint) for which an architectural analysis will be performed.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_LR24gM1vEd6r0fGOs-z5sw" name="Create an initial decomposition" guid="_LR24gM1vEd6r0fGOs-z5sw">
    <sectionDescription>Depending on the viewpoint type, decompose the system into its viewpoint/view-specific elements and outline the significant&#xD;
collaborations that realize the main system's operations.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_oeLBsM1vEd6r0fGOs-z5sw" name="Look for alternatives" guid="_oeLBsM1vEd6r0fGOs-z5sw">
    <sectionDescription>Based on your experience, on the existent and/or available assets, non-functional requirements, and other constraints,&#xD;
define alternate decompositions into main elements&amp;nbsp;and their associated collaborations.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_CjPtIM1wEd6r0fGOs-z5sw" name="Select candidate solutions" guid="_CjPtIM1wEd6r0fGOs-z5sw">
    <sectionDescription>Identify those solutions that will be considered as candidates for a detailed trade study analysis.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_Hx7YgM1wEd6r0fGOs-z5sw" name="Create Trade Study Report" guid="_Hx7YgM1wEd6r0fGOs-z5sw">
    <sectionDescription>Capture the selected candidate solutions in the Trade Study Report.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>There is always more than one way to realize&amp;nbsp;a main aspect of a system (viewpoint).&amp;nbsp;The objective of this stage&#xD;
is to identify possible solutions for each previously identified viewpoints.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
